track_notes: Before reaching the summit of the Col Du Granon, take the dirt road on the right that goes to the Col des Barteaux. From there start hiking along the ridge. The trail is well defined and stays on the safe side of the ridge. The N-facing is cliffy and should be avoided. A GPS is probably useful as there are a few summits along the ridge with similar altitudes. The summit of the Grande Peyrolle is reached after hiking 2.7 km from the Col des Barteaux. There is no sign indicating the summit so keep track of where you are along the ridge. The trail is not technically difficult and may require the use of hands only in a couple of spots.
You can go to F/AM-207 La Gardiole just after this :-)
